Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of affray. I take full responsibility for my actions and acknowledge the impact it had on those present at the bar.

On the night in question, I was overwhelmed by the emotions that surfaced upon discovering my boyfriend's infidelity. In a moment of anger and hurt, I confronted him at the bar where he was with his friends. I admit to making a threat, stating that I would acquire a gun and harm him if he didn't disclose the name of the other woman involved. It is crucial to note, however, that I had no access to firearms and the threat was solely verbal.

I deeply regret my actions and the fear I may have instilled in others present. I should have sought a more composed and less confrontational approach to handle my emotions. I acknowledge that my behavior was inappropriate and I take full responsibility for the impact it had on those around me.

I believe it is important to highlight that I have no previous criminal record. This incident is an isolated and uncharacteristic occurrence in my otherwise law-abiding life. Additionally, I want to emphasize my commitment to personal growth and self-improvement. I have been attending therapy sessions weekly in order to address the underlying issues that contributed to my emotional outburst that night. 

While this incident was undoubtedly distressing for all involved, I want to assure the court that I have taken significant steps towards making amends. I am committed to making compensation for the fear and unease caused that night. Moreover, I am determined to prevent any repetition of such behavior in the future. 

Your Honor, I stand here today, pleading guilty, with a genuine understanding of the consequences of my actions. I humbly request the court's leniency in considering the mitigating factors presented in this case. I am truly remorseful for my conduct and am committed to learning from this experience.

Thank you for allowing me to address the court.

Sincerely,
Chloe Mills

